Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - This paper deals with speech recognition and synthesis, which falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP) and speech processing. 
2. cs.SD (Sound) - The paper focuses on speech perception and production, which is related to sound processing. 
3. cs.SI (Signal Processing) - The paper deals with processing speech signals, which is a subfield of signal processing. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses deep learning techniques to develop the closed-loop speech chain model. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper uses neural networks for speech recognition and synthesis, which falls under the domain of neural computing.
